title: perf: Add error handling to load_data method
body: This commit adds error handling to the load_data method to catch any exceptions raised by the _reload method. If an exception is caught, the method will print an error message and return None. If the _reload method returns a non-empty DataFrame, the method will return the data. If the data is empty or None, the method will print a message and return None. Additionally, the reload argument has been renamed to reload_data for clarity.
